headline: Delta Electronics Receives Frost & Sullivan's 2025 Europe Company of the Year Recognition for Leadership in Integrated Energy Solutions
summary: Frost & Sullivan is pleased to announce that Delta Electronics (Delta) has been given the 2025 Europe Company of the Year Recognition in the integrated energy solutions industry for its strong overall performance in driving innovation, customer value, and sustainable growth. This highlights Delta's consistent leadership in shaping the transition toward a cleaner and more resilient energy future through its comprehensive portfolio of power, automation, and grid technologies.

headline: Why Delta Air Lines stock is 'not an attractive investment'
summary: Prairie Operating Company executive vice president of market strategy and TheBigSkinny.com founder Lou Basenese, Yahoo Finance Senior Reporter Brooke DiPalma, and Yahoo Finance Fed Correspondent Jennifer Schonberger join Opening Bid host Brian Sozzi to discuss Delta Air's (DAL) stock moves, especially in light of the US federal government shutdown and consumer health. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Opening Bid.

content.title: Why Delta Air Lines stock is 'not an attractive investment'
content.description:
Prairie Operating Company executive vice president of market strategy and TheBigSkinny.com founder Lou Basenese, Yahoo Finance Senior Reporter Brooke DiPalma, and Yahoo Finance Fed Correspondent Jennifer Schonberger join Opening Bid host Brian Sozzi to discuss Delta Air's (DAL) stock moves, especially in light of the US federal government shutdown and consumer health.

To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Opening Bid.
